  "claim_short": "0206107 Tokarev On sub B-convex Banach spaces Problem 1 asks whether any c-convex Banach space X generates a sub B-convex class X^f. Literal counterexample: X=l2 is c-convex with S(l2)={2}, but every sub B-convex class contains a representative l1 plus_1 W and hence has 1 in its l_p spectrum. Likely erratum-style edge case; intended non-B-convex c-convex variant remains open.",
